      "writtenOn": "2016-03-22T00:19:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I usually don\u0027t prefer this check.\nBasically, this only verifies that the returned error string is exactly some constant. This will only break when that constant changes, and will have to be updated to meet that same constant again...\nimo, that\u0027s testing implementation, not behaviour.\n\nBut I\u0027ve heard arguments on either side -- if you were to suddenly start returning some actually meaningful error message instead, this will catch that.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 45,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 45,
        "endChar": 70
      },
      "revId": "ee8c3cc1175ce3ce5458bc7f4c683ac9a4308bbf",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1cc45660_b8a455d1",
        "filename": "android/emulation/control/ApkInstaller_unittest.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 45,
      "author": {
        "id": 1079203
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-03-22T00:40:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "What about a happy medium: add a ApkInstaller:kDefaultErrorString that gets used everywhere so we only ever change one place, and the tests don\u0027t break?\n\nI think its important to have a test distinguishing between \"the output file couldn\u0027t be read for some reason\" and \"the output file says the install failed\", although based on what you\u0027ve said, the first shouldn\u0027t ever happen...",
      "parentUuid": "7c21d2e1_2b2a7e5c",
